> These juicy meatballs simmered in cannellini bean stew are inspired by the traditional Spanish dish 'albóndigas' which are a type of meatball. Another Iberian staple included in this meal is the iconic Catalan tapa 'pan con tomate'.

Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop half the @garlic{3%cloves}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it.

Roast the parcel until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press).

In a large #bowl, combine the @Irish beef mince{240%g}, half the grated garlic, @breadcrumbs{1%pack}, 2 tbsp @water{2%tbsp} and @salt{¼%tsp}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together by hand. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 3-4 per person.

Pop the meatballs onto a lined #baking tray{} and bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, cut the @ciabatta{2} into 1cm slices. Pop onto a separate baking tray. Toss with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a drizzle of @oil{}.

Bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @cannellini beans{1%pack} in a #sieve. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced).

Halve the @tomato{2}. Carefully grate the tomato with a #grater{} until you're left only with the skin (discard the skin).

Drizzle the grated tomato with a little @oil{} and @sugar{½%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Bean Stew ==

Place a large #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Add the onion and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once softened, add the @paprika{2%sachets} and remaining grated garlic.

Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Pour in half a sachet of @red wine vinegar{½%sachet} and allow to evaporate, ~{30%seconds}.

Next, stir in the cannellini beans, @passata{1%pack}, @red wine jus{1%sachet} and @sugar{½%tsp}. Cover and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the roasted garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors, squeeze it out of the skin and mash with a #fork. Stir through the grated tomato.

Once the meatballs are cooked through, stir them into the beans and simmer for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if desired. Add a splash of @water{to taste} if it's a little too thick.

== Pan Con Tomate ==

When everything's ready, spoon the tomato mixture over the crispy bread.

Divide your meatball and bean stew between serving #bowls.

Top with the @salad leaves{40%g} and drizzle over some @oil{}.

Serve your pan con tomate alongside.